definition.value: An indole phytoalexin that is indole substituted at position 3 by a 1,3-thiazol-2-yl group.

An organic heterotricyclic compound that is 5,6-dihydroimidazo[1,2-d][1,4]benzoxazepine substituted by 1-(propan-2-yl)-1H-1,2,4-triazol-5-yl and [(2S)-1-amino-1-oxopropan-2-yl]oxy groups at positions 2 and 9, respectively. It is a potent and selective inhibitor of PI3Kalpha (Ki = 0.2 nM).
A member of the class of piperidines that is piperidine substituted by a propyl group at position 2.
